      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This data type makes it possible to:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Create a new display configuration transaction using the function "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/1455235-cgbegindisplayconfiguration"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Record a set of configuration changes, each bound to one or more displays"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " Apply the changes in a single transaction using the function "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/1454488-cgcompletedisplayconfiguration"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ", or discard the changes using the function "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/1455522-cgcanceldisplayconfiguration"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "There are no restrictions on the order in which you accumulate configuration changes in a transaction. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Configuration changes sometimes conflict with each other. For example, a new origin might be rendered invalid by a subsequent configuration change. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If possible, Quartz uses a “best fit” strategy to resolve conflicts between configuration changes. For example, when you change the resolution of a single display in a two-display system, Quartz automatically retiles the displays to prevent separation or overlap of the adjoining edges."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
